  archivename: Ceasar Cypher
  image: {fileID: 0}
  date: 
  content: 'Ceasar Cypher:

    This cypher is quite simple. Text is encoded by shifting
    the alphabet by a number of places.

    Example encoded with 1 To the left:

    A
    => Z, B => A, C => B, D => C, E => D, F => E, G => F, H => G, I => H, J => I,
    K => J, L => K, M => L, N => M, O => N, P => O, Q => P, R => Q, S => R, T =>
    S, U => T, V => U, W => V, X => W, Y => X, Z => Y



'
  contentShort: Ceasar Cypher
  suspicious: 0
  notSuspicious: 0
  isSmall: 0
